Today marks 14 days since 112 people were placed in quarantine at that resort, about 25 kilometres outside Polokwane. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has declared the Ranch Resort in Limpopo, a green zone. The 112 people who were placed in quarantine after repatriation from China are in the clear. Ramaphosa was at the Ranch Resort in Limpopo on Sunday. The citizens will be reunited with their families after testing negative for coronavirus. The group was placed under quarantine on 14 March after they were repatriated from China following the outbreak of COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.